{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892237600,"sessionID":"ses_284932f3fffeWOnPF3XoJZVqgw","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6cf8cb001rtND6bAU5R4gxi","messageID":"msg_d7b6ce9460010AEM3yPKBrUzAb","sessionID":"ses_284932f3fffeWOnPF3XoJZVqgw","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_55b0abd3016640afb1dc5855","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041 E2E Integration Test Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This implementation provides comprehensive end-to-end (E2E) integration tests for the AgentCube platform, covering all major components and functionality.\n6: \n7: ## Files Created/Modified\n8: \n9: ### Core Test Files\n10: \n11: 1. **e2e_test.go** (16KB)\n12:    - Comprehensive Go test suite with 20+ test cases\n13:    - Tests: Health checks, agent invocation, session management, metrics, concurrent invocations, error handling\n14:    - Kubernetes integration tests for namespace isolation, resource quotas, ConfigMaps, ServiceAccounts\n15: \n16: 2. **test_codeinterpreter.py** (21KB)\n17:    - Comprehensive Python test suite with 20+ test cases\n18:    - Tests: Health checks, code execution, session lifecycle, load balancing, warm pool latency\n19:    - Advanced tests: Multi-step execution, error handling, resource management\n20: \n21: 3. **helpers.go** (4KB)\n22:    - Test configuration loading\n23:    - HTTP client utilities\n24:    - Retry logic with exponential backoff\n25:    - Endpoint health checking\n26:    - Random ID generation\n27: \n28: ### Test Fixtures (YAML)\n29: \n30: 4. **e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml**\n31:    - CodeInterpreter with warm pool configuration\n32:    - Min size: 2, Max size: 10\n33:    - Target utilization: 70%\n34: \n35: 5. **stress_test_agent.yaml**\n36:    - AgentRuntime with 3 replicas for load testing\n37:    - Random processing time simulation\n38:    - Metrics reporting\n39: \n40: 6. **multi_session_agent.yaml**\n41:    - AgentRuntime supporting multiple concurrent sessions\n42:    - Session state tracking\n43:    - Request counting\n44: \n45: 7. **e2e_advanced_interpreter.yaml**\n46:    - Python 3.11-based interpreter\n47:    - Enhanced security context\n48:    - Module allowlist\n49:    - Resource limits: 1 CPU, 1Gi memory\n50: \n51: ### Configuration & Scripts\n52: \n53: 8. **config.env**\n54:    - Environment variable definitions\n55:    - Test configuration parameters\n56:    - Color codes for output\n57: \n58: 9. **run_e2e.sh** (17KB)\n59:    - Enhanced test runner with:\n60:      - Structured logging (info, warn, error, debug, success)\n61:      - Automatic log collection on failure\n62:      - Test report generation (Markdown format)\n63:      - Prerequisite checking\n64:      - Cleanup handlers\n65:      - Command-line argument parsing\n66:      - Port forwarding management\n67:      - Health check validation\n68: \n69: 10. **README.md** (9KB)\n70:     - Comprehensive documentation\n71:     - Quick start guide\n72:     - Configuration reference\n73:     - Troubleshooting section\n74:     - Writing new tests guide\n75:     - CI/CD integration examples\n76: \n77: ## Test Coverage\n78: \n79: ### Go Tests (e2e_test.go)\n80: \n81: | Test | Purpose |\n82: |------|---------|\n83: | TestHealthCheck | Workload manager health endpoint |\n84: | TestRouterHealth | Router live health endpoint |\n85: | TestRouterReady | Router ready health endpoint |\n86: | TestInvokeEchoAgent | Echo agent invocation |\n87: | TestCodeInterpreter | Basic code execution |\n88: | TestSessionLifecycle | Kubernetes pod verification |\n89: | TestSessionCreationAndDeletion | Session API lifecycle |\n90: | TestMetricsEndpoint | Workload manager metrics |\n91: | TestRouterMetrics | Router metrics |\n92: | TestConcurrentInvocations | Parallel request handling |\n93: | TestInvalidAgentInvocation | Error handling for invalid agents |\n94: | TestMalformedRequest | JSON parsing error handling |\n95: | TestSessionTimeout | TTL expiration verification |\n96: | TestWarmPoolCodeInterpreter | Warm pool latency test |\n97: | TestNamespaceIsolation | Kubernetes namespace verification |\n98: | TestResourceQuotas | Resource quota checking |\n99: | TestConfigMapExists | ConfigMap discovery |\n100: | TestServiceAccounts | ServiceAccount verification |\n101: \n102: ### Python Tests (test_codeinterpreter.py)\n103: \n104: | Test | Purpose |\n105: |------|---------|\n106: | test_01_workload_manager_health | WM health check |\n107: | test_02_router_health_live | Router live health |\n108: | test_03_router_health_ready | Router ready check |\n109: | test_04_invoke_echo_agent | Echo agent test |\n110: | test_05_code_interpreter_basic | Basic code execution |\n111: | test_06_code_interpreter_math | Mathematical computation |\n112: | test_07_code_interpreter_data_processing | Data processing |\n113: | test_08_session_creation | Session lifecycle |\n114: | test_09_concurrent_invocations | Concurrent requests |\n115: | test_10_invalid_agent_invocation | Error handling |\n116: | test_11_malformed_request | JSON error handling |\n117: | test_12_metrics_endpoint | Metrics availability |\n118: | test_13_router_metrics | Router metrics |\n119: | test_14_warm_pool_latency | Warm pool performance |\n120: | test_15_code_execution_timeout | Timeout handling |\n121: | test_16_code_with_output_capture | stdout/stderr capture |\n122: | test_17_multi_step_code_execution | Session state |\n123: | test_18_code_interpreter_error_handling | Error reporting |\n124: | test_19_agent_runtime_status | Runtime status query |\n125: | test_20_load_balancing | Load distribution |\n126: \n127: ### Additional Test Classes\n128: \n129: - **TestNamespaceIsolation**: Multi-tenancy validation\n130: - **TestResourceManagement**: Quota enforcement\n131: \n132: ## Features Implemented\n133: \n134: ### Test Infrastructure\n135: \n136: 1. **Configuration Management**\n137:    - Environment variable loading\n138:    - Default values\n139:    - Timeout configuration\n140:    - Concurrency settings\n141: \n142: 2. **HTTP Client**\n143:    - Configurable base URLs\n144:    - Token-based authentication\n145:    - Timeout handling\n146:    - JSON serialization\n147: \n148: 3. **Test Helpers**\n149:    - Retry with exponential backoff\n150:    - Condition waiting\n151:    - Random ID generation\n152:    - Health check utilities\n153: \n154: 4. **Test Runner**\n155:    - Automated setup/teardown\n156:    - Log collection\n157:    - Report generation\n158:    - Error handling\n159:    - Port forwarding\n160: \n161: ### Test Coverage Areas\n162: \n163: 1. **Component Health**\n164:    - Workload Manager endpoints\n165:    - Router endpoints\n166:    - Readiness probes\n167: \n168: 2. **Agent Invocation**\n169:    - Echo agent\n170:    - Code interpreter\n171:    - Invalid agents\n172:    - Malformed requests\n173: \n174: 3. **Session Management**\n175:    - Creation\n176:    - Invocation\n177:    - Deletion\n178:    - Timeout handling\n179: \n180: 4. **Performance**\n181:    - Concurrent invocations\n182:    - Warm pool latency\n183:    - Load balancing\n184: \n185: 5. **Kubernetes Integration**\n186:    - Namespace isolation\n187:    - Resource quotas\n188:    - ConfigMaps\n189:    - ServiceAccounts\n190:    - Pod lifecycle\n191: \n192: 6. **Observability**\n193:    - Metrics endpoints\n194:    - Log collection\n195:    - Event monitoring\n196: \n197: ## Usage\n198: \n199: ### Quick Start\n200: \n201: ```bash\n202: # Run full test suite\n203: make e2e\n204: \n205: # Or directly\n206: ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### Manual Testing\n210: \n211: ```bash\n212: # Set up environment\n213: export WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://localhost:8080\n214: export ROUTER_URL=http://localhost:8081\n215: export API_TOKEN=$(kubectl -n agentcube create token e2e-test --duration=24h)\n216: \n217: # Run Go tests\n218: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n219: \n220: # Run Python tests\n221: cd test/e2e\n222: python test_codeinterpreter.py --verbose\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ### Advanced Options\n226: \n227: ```bash\n228: # Preserve cluster for debugging\n229: ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh --preserve-cluster\n230: \n231: # Skip setup (use existing cluster)\n232: ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh --skip-setup\n233: \n234: # Enable debug logging\n235: ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh --debug\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ## Test Results\n239: \n240: ### Expected Output\n241: \n242: ```\n243: =========================================\n244:   AgentCube E2E Test Suite\n245: =========================================\n246: \n247: [INFO] Configuration:\n248: [INFO]   Cluster: agentcube-e2e\n249: [INFO]   Namespace: agentcube\n250: [INFO]   Artifacts: /path/to/e2e-logs\n251: \n252: [STEP] Checking prerequisites...\n253: [SUCCESS] All prerequisites installed\n254: \n255: [STEP] Setting up E2E environment...\n256: [INFO] Creating Kind cluster 'agentcube-e2e'...\n257: ...\n258: [SUCCESS] E2E environment setup complete!\n259: \n260: [STEP] Running E2E tests...\n261: ✓ Workload Manager health: ok\n262: ✓ Router live health check passed\n263: ✓ Router ready check passed\n264: ✓ Echo agent invocation successful\n265: ✓ Code interpreter execution successful\n266: ...\n267: \n268: ========================================\n269: E2E Test Summary\n270: ========================================\n271: Total Tests:    40+\n272: Passed:         38+\n273: Failed:         0\n274: Skipped:        2+\n275: Total Time:     180s\n276: ========================================\n277: STATUS: PASSED\n278: ```\n279: \n280: ### Artifacts\n281: \n282: On completion (or failure), the following artifacts are generated:\n283: \n284: - `test_report_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.md` - Markdown test report\n285: - `workloadmanager_*.log` - Workload manager logs\n286: - `router_*.log` - Router logs\n287: - `sandbox_*.log` - Sandbox controller logs\n288: - `events_*.txt` - Kubernetes events\n289: - `pods_*.txt` - Pod status\n290: - `*_describe_*.txt` - Resource descriptions\n291: \n292: ## Best Practices Followed\n293: \n294: 1. **Go Conventions**\n295:    - Proper error handling\n296:    - Deferred cleanup\n297:    - Table-driven tests where appropriate\n298:    - Descriptive test names\n299: \n300: 2. **Python Conventions**\n301:    - unittest.TestCase structure\n302:    - setUpClass for shared setup\n303:    - Docstrings for all tests\n304:    - Proper exception handling\n305: \n306: 3. **Test Design**\n307:    - Isolated test cases\n308:    - Idempotent operations\n309:    - Clean resource management\n310:    - Comprehensive logging\n311:    - Graceful degradation (skip vs fail)\n312: \n313: 4. **Error Handling**\n314:    - Timeout protection\n315:    - Retry logic\n316:    - Detailed error messages\n317:    - Automatic log collection\n318: \n319: ## CI/CD Integration\n320: \n321: ### GitHub Actions Example\n322: \n323: ```yaml\n324: name: E2E Tests\n325: \n326: on: [push, pull_request]\n327: \n328: jobs:\n329:   e2e:\n330:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n331:     steps:\n332:       - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n333:       \n334:       - name: Set up Go\n335:         uses: actions/setup-go@v4\n336:         with:\n337:           go-version: '1.23'\n338:       \n339:       - name: Set up Python\n340:         uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n341:         with:\n342:           python-version: '3.10'\n343:       \n344:       - name: Install dependencies\n345:         run: |\n346:           go mod download\n347:           pip install -e ./sdk-python\n348:       \n349:       - name: Run E2E Tests\n350:         run: make e2e\n351:       \n352:       - name: Upload artifacts\n353:         if: always()\n354:         uses: actions/upload-artifact@v3\n355:         with:\n356:           name: e2e-logs\n357:           path: e2e-logs/\n358: ```\n359: \n360: ## Future Enhancements\n361: \n362: Potential areas for expansion:\n363: \n364: 1. **Performance Testing**\n365:    - Benchmark tests\n366:    - Latency percentile tracking\n367:    - Resource utilization metrics\n368: \n369: 2. **Chaos Testing**\n370:    - Pod failure scenarios\n371:    - Network partition tests\n372:    - Resource exhaustion\n373: \n374: 3. **Security Testing**\n375:    - RBAC validation\n376:    - Token expiration tests\n377:    - Namespace isolation verification\n378: \n379: 4. **Integration Tests**\n380:    - External service mocking\n381:    - Multi-cluster scenarios\n382:    - Cross-region testing\n383: \n384: ## Compliance\n385: \n386: - ✅ Go 1.23+ compatible\n387: - ✅ Python 3.10+ compatible\n388: - ✅ Kubernetes 1.28+ compatible\n389: - ✅ Follows Go testing conventions\n390: - ✅ Follows Python unittest conventions\n391: - ✅ Matches AgentCube project structure\n392: - ✅ Comprehensive error handling\n393: - ✅ No placeholders or TODOs\n394: - ✅ Complete, working code\n395: \n396: ## Verification\n397: \n398: All code has been verified:\n399: \n400: ```bash\n401: # Go compilation\n402: go build ./test/e2e/...  # ✓ Success\n403: \n404: # Python syntax\n405: python3 -m py_compile test/e2e/test_codeinterpreter.py  # ✓ Success\n406: \n407: # File permissions\n408: chmod +x test/e2e/run_e2e.sh  # ✓ Applied\n409: ```\n410: \n411: ## Support\n412: \n413: For questions or issues:\n414: 1. Review README.md\n415: 2. Check troubleshooting section\n416: 3. Examine test artifacts\n417: 4. Open GitHub issue\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n421: **Implementation Date**: 2026-04-11\n422: **Module**: test/e2e\n423: **Language**: Go, Python, Bash\n424: **Size**: L (Large)\n425: **Status**: ✅ Complete\n\n(End of file - total 425 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-041 E2E Integration Test Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\n\nThis implementation provides comprehensive end-to-end (E2E) integration tests for the AgentCube platform, covering all major components and functionality.\n\n## Files Created/Modified\n\n### Core Test Files\n\n1. **e2e_test.go** (16KB)\n   - Comprehensive Go test suite with 20+ test cases\n   - Tests: Health checks, agent invocation, session management, metrics, concurrent invocations, error handling\n   - Kubernetes integration tests for namespace isolation, resource quotas, ConfigMaps, ServiceAccounts\n\n2. **test_codeinterpreter.py** (21KB)\n   - Comprehensive Python test suite with 20+ test cases\n   - Tests: Health checks, code execution, session lifecycle, load balancing, warm pool latency\n   - Advanced tests: Multi-step execution, error handling, resource management\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775892237571,"end":1775892237598}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892237602,"sessionID":"ses_284932f3fffeWOnPF3XoJZVqgw","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6cfe200013iLLHhfwYZVhA6","messageID":"msg_d7b6ce9460010AEM3yPKBrUzAb","sessionID":"ses_284932f3fffeWOnPF3XoJZVqgw","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9ac512f056c14197973cb3de","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube E2E Tests\n2: \n3: This directory contains comprehensive end-to-end tests for the AgentCube platform.\n4: \n5: ## Table of Contents\n6: \n7: - [Overview](#overview)\n8: - [Requirements](#requirements)\n9: - [Quick Start](#quick-start)\n10: - [Test Structure](#test-structure)\n11: - [Configuration](#configuration)\n12: - [Running Tests](#running-tests)\n13: - [Test Fixtures](#test-fixtures)\n14: - [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting)\n15: - [Writing New Tests](#writing-new-tests)\n16: \n17: ## Overview\n18: \n19: The E2E test suite validates the complete AgentCube platform including:\n20: \n21: - **Workload Manager**: Health checks, session management, metrics\n22: - **Router**: Health checks, agent invocation, load balancing\n23: - **Code Interpreter**: Code execution, session lifecycle, warm pool\n24: - **Kubernetes Integration**: Namespace isolation, resource quotas, RBAC\n25: - **Agent Runtimes**: Echo agent, stress test agent, multi-session agent\n26: \n27: ## Requirements\n28: \n29: ### Software Requirements\n30: \n31: - **Go** 1.23+\n32: - **Python** 3.10+\n33: - **Kind** v0.30.0+\n34: - **Helm** 3.x\n35: - **Docker** 20.10+\n36: - **kubectl** 1.28+\n37: \n38: ### System Requirements\n39: \n40: - 4+ CPU cores recommended\n41: - 8GB+ RAM recommended\n42: - Docker daemon running\n43: \n44: ## Quick Start\n45: \n46: Run the complete E2E test suite:\n47: \n48: ```bash\n49: # Full test suite (creates Kind cluster, runs tests, cleans up)\n50: make e2e\n51: \n52: # Or run the script directly\n53: ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ## Test Structure\n57: \n58: ```\n59: test/e2e/\n60: ├── config.env                    # Environment configuration\n61: ├── helpers.go                    # Go test helpers\n62: ├── e2e_test.go                   # Go E2E tests\n63: ├── __init__.py                   # Python package init\n64: ├── test_codeinterpreter.py       # Python E2E tests\n65: ├── run_e2e.sh                    # Test runner script\n66: ├── README.md                     # This file\n67: └── fixtures/\n68:     ├── echo_agent.yaml           # Echo agent fixture\n69:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml # Basic code interpreter\n70:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml  # Warm pool interpreter\n71:     ├── stress_test_agent.yaml    # Stress test agent\n72:     ├── multi_session_agent.yaml  # Multi-session agent\n73:     └── e2e_advanced_interpreter.yaml # Advanced interpreter\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ## Configuration\n77: \n78: ### Environment Variables\n79: \n80: | Variable | Default | Description |\n81: |----------|---------|-------------|\n82: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` | Kind cluster name |\n83: | `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER` | `true` | Delete cluster before tests |\n84: | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP` | `false` | Skip cluster setup |\n85: | `E2E_PRESERVE_CLUSTER` | `false` | Keep cluster after tests |\n86: | `E2E_DEBUG` | `false` | Enable debug logging |\n87: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `agentcube` | Kubernetes namespace |\n88: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `v0.1.1` | Agent sandbox version |\n89: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` | `8080` | Workload manager port |\n90: | `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` | `8081` | Router port |\n91: | `REDIS_IMAGE` | `redis:7-alpine` | Redis image |\n92: | `E2E_VENV_DIR` | `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv` | Python venv path |\n93: | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` | `${PWD}/e2e-logs` | Test artifacts path |\n94: | `E2E_TIMEOUT` | `30s` | HTTP request timeout |\n95: | `E2E_CONCURRENCY` | `5` | Concurrent test workers |\n96: \n97: ### Using Configuration File\n98: \n99: Source the configuration file:\n100: \n101: ```bash\n102: source test/e2e/config.env\n103: export E2E_CLUSTER_NAME=my-e2e-cluster\n104: ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ## Running Tests\n108: \n109: ### Full Test Suite\n110: \n111: ```bash\n112: # Run everything\n113: make e2e\n114: \n115: # With options\n116: ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh --skip-setup --preserve-cluster --debug\n117: ```\n118: \n119: ### Individual Test Suites\n120: \n121: ```bash\n122: # Go tests only\n123: export WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://localhost:8080\n124: export ROUTER_URL=http://localhost:8081\n125: export API_TOKEN=$(kubectl -n agentcube create token e2e-test --duration=24h)\n126: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n127: \n128: # Python tests only\n129: cd test/e2e\n130: python test_codeinterpreter.py --verbose\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### Manual Testing\n134: \n135: ```bash\n136: # Set up port forwarding\n137: kubectl -n agentcube port-forward svc/workloadmanager 8080:8080 &\n138: kubectl -n agentcube port-forward svc/agentcube-router 8081:8080 &\n139: \n140: # Test health endpoints\n141: curl http://localhost:8080/health\n142: curl http://localhost:8081/health/live\n143: \n144: # Test agent invocation\n145: curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/invoke/echo-agent \\\n146:   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n147:   -d '{\"message\": \"Hello!\"}'\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ## Test Fixtures\n151: \n152: ### Echo Agent\n153: \n154: Simple agent that echoes back received messages.\n155: \n156: ```yaml\n157: kubectl apply -f test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml\n158: ```\n159: \n160: ### Code Interpreter\n161: \n162: Python code execution environment.\n163: \n164: ```yaml\n165: kubectl apply -f test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### Warm Pool Interpreter\n169: \n170: Code interpreter with pre-warmed sessions for low latency.\n171: \n172: ```yaml\n173: kubectl apply -f test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ### Stress Test Agent\n177: \n178: Agent designed for load testing with multiple replicas.\n179: \n180: ```yaml\n181: kubectl apply -f test/e2e/stress_test_agent.yaml\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### Multi-Session Agent\n185: \n186: Agent that maintains state across multiple sessions.\n187: \n188: ```yaml\n189: kubectl apply -f test/e2e/multi_session_agent.yaml\n190: ```\n191: \n192: ## Troubleshooting\n193: \n194: ### Test Failures\n195: \n196: 1. **Check logs**:\n197:    ```bash\n198:    ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh 2>&1 | tee e2e.log\n199:    ```\n200: \n201: 2. **View component logs**:\n202:    ```bash\n203:    kubectl -n agentcube logs -l app=workloadmanager\n204:    kubectl -n agentcube logs -l app=agentcube-router\n205:    ```\n206: \n207: 3. **Check pod status**:\n208:    ```bash\n209:    kubectl -n agentcube get pods -o wide\n210:    kubectl -n agentcube describe pod -l app=workloadmanager\n211:    ```\n212: \n213: 4. **View events**:\n214:    ```bash\n215:    kubectl -n agentcube get events --sort-by='.lastTimestamp'\n216:    ```\n217: \n218: ### Common Issues\n219: \n220: #### Port Already in Use\n221: \n222: ```bash\n223: # Kill existing port-forward processes\n224: pkill -f \"kubectl.*port-forward\"\n225: \n226: # Or use different ports\n227: export WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT=9080\n228: export ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT=9081\n229: ```\n230: \n231: #### Cluster Creation Fails\n232: \n233: ```bash\n234: # Delete existing cluster\n235: kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n236: \n237: # Recreate\n238: kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n239: ```\n240: \n241: #### Image Pull Errors\n242: \n243: ```bash\n244: # Build images\n245: make docker-build\n246: make docker-build-router\n247: \n248: # Load to Kind\n249: kind load docker-image workloadmanager:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n250: kind load docker-image agentcube-router:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n251: ```\n252: \n253: ### Collecting Artifacts\n254: \n255: On failure, artifacts are automatically collected to `$ARTIFACTS_PATH`:\n256: \n257: - Component logs\n258: - Pod descriptions\n259: - Kubernetes events\n260: - Test reports\n261: - Metrics snapshots\n262: \n263: ```bash\n264: # View artifacts\n265: ls -la $ARTIFACTS_PATH\n266: cat $ARTIFACTS_PATH/test_report_*.md\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ## Writing New Tests\n270: \n271: ### Go Tests\n272: \n273: ```go\n274: func TestMyFeature(t *testing.T) {\n275:     // Setup\n276:     payload := map[string]string{\n277:         \"message\": \"Test message\",\n278:     }\n279:     body, _ := json.Marshal(payload)\n280:     \n281:     // Execute\n282:     req, _ := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/my-agent\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n283:     req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n284:     resp, err := client.Do(req)\n285:     \n286:     // Assert\n287:     if err != nil {\n288:         t.Fatalf(\"Request failed: %v\", err)\n289:     }\n290:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n291:     \n292:     if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n293:         t.Fatalf(\"Expected 200, got %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n294:     }\n295:     \n296:     var result map[string]interface{}\n297:     json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result)\n298:     \n299:     if result[\"status\"] != \"success\" {\n300:         t.Errorf(\"Expected success status\")\n301:     }\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ### Python Tests\n306: \n307: ```python\n308: def test_my_feature(self):\n309:     \"\"\"Test my feature.\"\"\"\n310:     payload = {\n311:         'message': 'Test message'\n312:     }\n313:     \n314:     try:\n315:         result = self.router_client.request(\n316:             'POST',\n317:             '/invoke/my-agent',\n318:             data=payload\n319:         )\n320:         self.assertEqual(result.get('status'), 'success')\n321:         print(f\"✓ My feature test passed\")\n322:     except Exception as e:\n323:         self.fail(f\"My feature test failed: {e}\")\n324: ```\n325: \n326: ### Test Best Practices\n327: \n328: 1. **Use descriptive names**: `TestSessionCreationAndDeletion`\n329: 2. **Clean up resources**: Delete sessions, pods, etc.\n330: 3. **Handle errors gracefully**: Use `t.Skip()` for optional features\n331: 4. **Add logging**: Use `t.Logf()` or `print()` for visibility\n332: 5. **Set timeouts**: Prevent hanging tests\n333: 6. **Test edge cases**: Invalid inputs, timeouts, errors\n334: 7. **Use fixtures**: Reusable test data and configurations\n335: \n336: ## CI/CD Integration\n337: \n338: ### GitHub Actions\n339: \n340: ```yaml\n341: - name: Run E2E Tests\n342:   run: |\n343:     make e2e\n344:   env:\n345:     E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER: true\n346:     ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n347: \n348: - name: Upload Artifacts\n349:   if: always()\n350:   uses: actions/upload-artifact@v3\n351:   with:\n352:     name: e2e-logs\n353:     path: e2e-logs/\n354: ```\n355: \n356: ### Local CI\n357: \n358: ```bash\n359: # Run in CI mode\n360: export E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true\n361: export E2E_SKIP_SETUP=false\n362: ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ## Performance Testing\n366: \n367: ### Load Testing\n368: \n369: ```bash\n370: # Configure load test parameters\n371: export E2E_CONCURRENCY=10\n372: export E2E_LOAD_TEST_INVOCATIONS=100\n373: \n374: # Run stress tests\n375: go test -v ./test/e2e/... -run TestConcurrentInvocations\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### Latency Testing\n379: \n380: ```bash\n381: # Test warm pool latency\n382: curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/invoke/e2e-code-interpreter-warmpool \\\n383:   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n384:   -d '{\"code\": \"import time; start = time.time(); print(time.time() - start)\"}'\n385: ```\n386: \n387: ## Security Considerations\n388: \n389: - Tests run with limited RBAC permissions\n390: - Service accounts are namespace-scoped\n391: - API tokens have short TTLs (24h)\n392: - No production credentials are used\n393: \n394: ## Support\n395: \n396: For issues or questions:\n397: - Check troubleshooting section\n398: - Review test logs in `$ARTIFACTS_PATH`\n399: - Open an issue on GitHub\n\n(End of file - total 399 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube E2E Tests\n\nThis directory contains comprehensive end-to-end tests for the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [Requirements](#requirements)\n- [Quick Start](#quick-start)\n- [Test Structure](#test-structure)\n- [Configuration](#configuration)\n- [Running Tests](#running-tests)\n- [Test Fixtures](#test-fixtures)\n- [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting)\n- [Writing New Tests](#writing-new-tests)\n\n## Overview\n\nThe E2E test suite validates the complete AgentCube platform including:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/README.md","time":{"start":1775892237574,"end":1775892237600}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892237603,"sessionID":"ses_284932f3fffeWOnPF3XoJZVqgw","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6d02e9001h5FFZsJZAriuAZ","messageID":"msg_d7b6ce9460010AEM3yPKBrUzAb","sessionID":"ses_284932f3fffeWOnPF3XoJZVqgw","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4b57fbb23424454c912babd5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/e2e_test.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/e2e_test.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // Copyright 2026 AgentCube Authors\n2: // E2E tests for AgentCube\n3: \n4: package e2e\n5: \n6: import (\n7: \t\"bytes\"\n8: \t\"context\"\n9: \t\"encoding/json\"\n10: \t\"fmt\"\n11: \t\"io\"\n12: \t\"net/http\"\n13: \t\"os\"\n14: \t\"testing\"\n15: \t\"time\"\n16: \n17: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n18: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n19: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n20: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n21: )\n22: \n23: var (\n24: \tworkloadManagerURL string\n25: \trouterURL          string\n26: \tapiToken           string\n27: \tclient             *http.Client\n28: \tk8sClient          *kubernetes.Clientset\n29: \tnamespace          string\n30: )\n31: \n32: func TestMain(m *testing.M) {\n33: \tworkloadManagerURL = os.Getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n34: \trouterURL = os.Getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n35: \tapiToken = os.Getenv(\"API_TOKEN\")\n36: \tnamespace = os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\")\n37: \n38: \tif workloadManagerURL == \"\" {\n39: \t\tworkloadManagerURL = \"http://localhost:8080\"\n40: \t}\n41: \tif routerURL == \"\" {\n42: \t\trouterURL = \"http://localhost:8081\"\n43: \t}\n44: \tif namespace == \"\" {\n45: \t\tnamespace = \"agentcube\"\n46: \t}\n47: \tif apiToken == \"\" {\n48: \t\tfmt.Println(\"Warning: API_TOKEN not set\")\n49: \t}\n50: \n51: \tclient = &http.Client{\n52: \t\tTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \tkubeconfig := os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\")\n56: \tif kubeconfig == \"\" {\n57: \t\thome, _ := os.UserHomeDir()\n58: \t\tkubeconfig = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/.kube/config\", home)\n59: \t}\n60: \n61: \tconfig, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfig)\n62: \tif err == nil {\n63: \t\tk8sClient, _ = kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n64: \t}\n65: \n66: \tos.Exit(m.Run())\n67: }\n68: \n69: func TestHealthCheck(t *testing.T) {\n70: \tresp, err := client.Get(workloadManagerURL + \"/health\")\n71: \tif err != nil {\n72: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Health check failed: %v\", err)\n73: \t}\n74: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n75: \n76: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n77: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Health check returned status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n78: \t}\n79: \n80: \tbody, err := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n81: \tif err != nil {\n82: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to read response body: %v\", err)\n83: \t}\n84: \n85: \tvar health struct {\n86: \t\tStatus string `json:\"status\"`\n87: \t}\n88: \tif err := json.Unmarshal(body, &health); err != nil {\n89: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to parse health response: %v\", err)\n90: \t}\n91: \n92: \tif health.Status != \"ok\" && health.Status != \"healthy\" {\n93: \t\tt.Logf(\"Health status: %s\", health.Status)\n94: \t}\n95: }\n96: \n97: func TestRouterHealth(t *testing.T) {\n98: \tresp, err := client.Get(routerURL + \"/health/live\")\n99: \tif err != nil {\n100: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Router health check failed: %v\", err)\n101: \t}\n102: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n103: \n104: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n105: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Router health check returned status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n106: \t}\n107: }\n108: \n109: func TestRouterReady(t *testing.T) {\n110: \tresp, err := client.Get(routerURL + \"/health/ready\")\n111: \tif err != nil {\n112: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Router ready check failed: %v\", err)\n113: \t}\n114: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n115: \n116: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n117: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Router ready check returned status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n118: \t}\n119: \n120: \tbody, err := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n121: \tif err != nil {\n122: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to read response body: %v\", err)\n123: \t}\n124: \n125: \tvar ready struct {\n126: \t\tReady bool `json:\"ready\"`\n127: \t}\n128: \tif err := json.Unmarshal(body, &ready); err != nil {\n129: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to parse ready response: %v\", err)\n130: \t}\n131: \n132: \tif !ready.Ready {\n133: \t\tt.Fatal(\"Router is not ready\")\n134: \t}\n135: }\n136: \n137: func TestInvokeEchoAgent(t *testing.T) {\n138: \tmessage := map[string]string{\n139: \t\t\"message\": \"Hello, echo agent!\",\n140: \t}\n141: \tbody, _ := json.Marshal(message)\n142: \n143: \treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/echo-agent\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n144: \tif err != nil {\n145: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create request: %v\", err)\n146: \t}\n147: \n148: \treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n149: \tif apiToken != \"\" {\n150: \t\treq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n151: \t}\n152: \n153: \tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n154: \tif err != nil {\n155: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Invoke request failed: %v\", err)\n156: \t}\n157: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n158: \n159: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n160: \t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n161: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Invoke returned status: %d, body: %s\", resp.StatusCode, string(body))\n162: \t}\n163: \n164: \tvar result map[string]interface{}\n165: \tif err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n166: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to decode response: %v\", err)\n167: \t}\n168: \n169: \tt.Logf(\"Echo agent response: %+v\", result)\n170: \n171: \tif status, ok := result[\"status\"].(string); !ok || status != \"success\" {\n172: \t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected status 'success', got '%v'\", result[\"status\"])\n173: \t}\n174: }\n175: \n176: func TestCodeInterpreter(t *testing.T) {\n177: \tcode := map[string]string{\n178: \t\t\"code\": \"print('Hello from code interpreter')\",\n179: \t}\n180: \tbody, _ := json.Marshal(code)\n181: \n182: \treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/e2e-code-interpreter\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n183: \tif err != nil {\n184: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create request: %v\", err)\n185: \t}\n186: \n187: \treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n188: \tif apiToken != \"\" {\n189: \t\treq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n190: \t}\n191: \n192: \tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n193: \tif err != nil {\n194: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Code interpreter request failed: %v\", err)\n195: \t}\n196: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n197: \n198: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n199: \t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n200: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Code interpreter returned status: %d, body: %s\", resp.StatusCode, string(body))\n201: \t}\n202: \n203: \tvar result map[string]interface{}\n204: \tif err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n205: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to decode response: %v\", err)\n206: \t}\n207: \n208: \tt.Logf(\"Code interpreter response: %+v\", result)\n209: }\n210: \n211: func TestSessionLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n212: \tif k8sClient == nil {\n213: \t\tt.Skip(\"Kubernetes client not available\")\n214: \t}\n215: \n216: \tctx := context.Background()\n217: \n218: \tpods, err := k8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{\n219: \t\tLabelSelector: \"app=workloadmanager\",\n220: \t})\n221: \tif err != nil {\n222: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to list pods: %v\", err)\n223: \t}\n224: \n225: \tif len(pods.Items) == 0 {\n226: \t\tt.Fatal(\"No workload manager pods found\")\n227: \t}\n228: \n229: \tfor _, pod := range pods.Items {\n230: \t\tif pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning {\n231: \t\t\tt.Logf(\"Found running workload manager pod: %s\", pod.Name)\n232: \t\t\treturn\n233: \t\t}\n234: \t}\n235: \n236: \tt.Fatal(\"No running workload manager pods found\")\n237: }\n238: \n239: func TestSessionCreationAndDeletion(t *testing.T) {\n240: \tsessionPayload := map[string]interface{}{\n241: \t\t\"interpreter\": \"e2e-code-interpreter\",\n242: \t\t\"namespace\":   namespace,\n243: \t\t\"ttl\":         \"60s\",\n244: \t}\n245: \tbody, _ := json.Marshal(sessionPayload)\n246: \n247: \treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", workloadManagerURL+\"/api/v1/sessions\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n248: \tif err != nil {\n249: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create session request: %v\", err)\n250: \t}\n251: \n252: \treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n253: \tif apiToken != \"\" {\n254: \t\treq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n255: \t}\n256: \n257: \tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n258: \tif err != nil {\n259: \t\tt.Skipf(\"Session creation not available: %v\", err)\n260: \t}\n261: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n262: \n263: \tif resp.StatusCode == http.StatusNotFound {\n264: \t\tt.Skip(\"Sessions API not available\")\n265: \t}\n266: \n267: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK && resp.StatusCode != http.StatusCreated {\n268: \t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n269: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Session creation returned status: %d, body: %s\", resp.StatusCode, string(body))\n270: \t}\n271: \n272: \tvar result map[string]interface{}\n273: \tif err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n274: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to decode session response: %v\", err)\n275: \t}\n276: \n277: \tsessionID, ok := result[\"sessionId\"].(string)\n278: \tif !ok {\n279: \t\tt.Fatal(\"Session ID not returned\")\n280: \t}\n281: \n282: \tt.Logf(\"Created session: %s\", sessionID)\n283: \n284: \tdeleteReq, err := http.NewRequest(\"DELETE\", workloadManagerURL+\"/api/v1/sessions/\"+sessionID, nil)\n285: \tif err != nil {\n286: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create delete request: %v\", err)\n287: \t}\n288: \n289: \tif apiToken != \"\" {\n290: \t\tdeleteReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n291: \t}\n292: \n293: \tdeleteResp, err := client.Do(deleteReq)\n294: \tif err != nil {\n295: \t\tt.Logf(\"Session deletion not available: %v\", err)\n296: \t\treturn\n297: \t}\n298: \tdefer deleteResp.Body.Close()\n299: \n300: \tt.Logf(\"Session deletion status: %d\", deleteResp.StatusCode)\n301: }\n302: \n303: func TestMetricsEndpoint(t *testing.T) {\n304: \tresp, err := client.Get(workloadManagerURL + \"/metrics\")\n305: \tif err != nil {\n306: \t\tt.Skipf(\"Metrics endpoint not available: %v\", err)\n307: \t}\n308: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n309: \n310: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n311: \t\tt.Skipf(\"Metrics returned status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n312: \t}\n313: \n314: \tbody, err := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n315: \tif err != nil {\n316: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to read metrics: %v\", err)\n317: \t}\n318: \n319: \tif len(body) == 0 {\n320: \t\tt.Fatal(\"Metrics body is empty\")\n321: \t}\n322: \n323: \tt.Logf(\"Metrics endpoint returned %d bytes\", len(body))\n324: }\n325: \n326: func TestRouterMetrics(t *testing.T) {\n327: \tresp, err := client.Get(routerURL + \"/metrics\")\n328: \tif err != nil {\n329: \t\tt.Skipf(\"Router metrics endpoint not available: %v\", err)\n330: \t}\n331: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n332: \n333: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n334: \t\tt.Skipf(\"Router metrics returned status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n335: \t}\n336: \n337: \tbody, err := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n338: \tif err != nil {\n339: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to read router metrics: %v\", err)\n340: \t}\n341: \n342: \tif len(body) == 0 {\n343: \t\tt.Fatal(\"Router metrics body is empty\")\n344: \t}\n345: \n346: \tt.Logf(\"Router metrics endpoint returned %d bytes\", len(body))\n347: }\n348: \n349: func TestConcurrentInvocations(t *testing.T) {\n350: \tconcurrency := 5\n351: \terrors := make(chan error, concurrency)\n352: \tsuccesses := make(chan bool, concurrency)\n353: \n354: \tfor i := 0; i < concurrency; i++ {\n355: \t\tgo func(id int) {\n356: \t\t\tmessage := map[string]string{\n357: \t\t\t\t\"message\": fmt.Sprintf(\"Concurrent test %d\", id),\n358: \t\t\t}\n359: \t\t\tbody, _ := json.Marshal(message)\n360: \n361: \t\t\treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/echo-agent\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n362: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n363: \t\t\t\terrors <- err\n364: \t\t\t\treturn\n365: \t\t\t}\n366: \n367: \t\t\treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n368: \t\t\tif apiToken != \"\" {\n369: \t\t\t\treq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n370: \t\t\t}\n371: \n372: \t\t\tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n373: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n374: \t\t\t\terrors <- err\n375: \t\t\t\treturn\n376: \t\t\t}\n377: \t\t\tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n378: \n379: \t\t\tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n380: \t\t\t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n381: \t\t\t\terrors <- fmt.Errorf(\"status %d: %s\", resp.StatusCode, string(body))\n382: \t\t\t\treturn\n383: \t\t\t}\n384: \n385: \t\t\tsuccesses <- true\n386: \t\t}(i)\n387: \t}\n388: \n389: \tsuccessCount := 0\n390: \terrorCount := 0\n391: \n392: \tfor i := 0; i < concurrency; i++ {\n393: \t\tselect {\n394: \t\tcase <-successes:\n395: \t\t\tsuccessCount++\n396: \t\tcase err := <-errors:\n397: \t\t\tt.Logf(\"Concurrent invocation error: %v\", err)\n398: \t\t\terrorCount++\n399: \t\tcase <-time.After(10 * time.Second):\n400: \t\t\tt.Fatal(\"Timeout waiting for concurrent invocations\")\n401: \t\t}\n402: \t}\n403: \n404: \tt.Logf(\"Concurrent test: %d successes, %d errors\", successCount, errorCount)\n405: \n406: \tif successCount < concurrency-1 {\n407: \t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected at least %d successes, got %d\", concurrency-1, successCount)\n408: \t}\n409: }\n410: \n411: func TestInvalidAgentInvocation(t *testing.T) {\n412: \tmessage := map[string]string{\n413: \t\t\"message\": \"Test invalid agent\",\n414: \t}\n415: \tbody, _ := json.Marshal(message)\n416: \n417: \treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/non-existent-agent\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n418: \tif err != nil {\n419: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create request: %v\", err)\n420: \t}\n421: \n422: \treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n423: \tif apiToken != \"\" {\n424: \t\treq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n425: \t}\n426: \n427: \tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n428: \tif err != nil {\n429: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Request failed: %v\", err)\n430: \t}\n431: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n432: \n433: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusNotFound && resp.StatusCode != http.StatusBadRequest {\n434: \t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n435: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Expected 404 or 400, got status: %d, body: %s\", resp.StatusCode, string(body))\n436: \t}\n437: \n438: \tt.Logf(\"Invalid agent correctly rejected with status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n439: }\n440: \n441: func TestMalformedRequest(t *testing.T) {\n442: \tbody := []byte(\"invalid json\")\n443: \n444: \treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/echo-agent\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n445: \tif err != nil {\n446: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create request: %v\", err)\n447: \t}\n448: \n449: \treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n450: \tif apiToken != \"\" {\n451: \t\treq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n452: \t}\n453: \n454: \tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n455: \tif err != nil {\n456: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Request failed: %v\", err)\n457: \t}\n458: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n459: \n460: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusBadRequest {\n461: \t\tt.Logf(\"Malformed request status: %d (expected 400)\", resp.StatusCode)\n462: \t}\n463: \n464: \tt.Logf(\"Malformed request correctly rejected with status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n465: }\n466: \n467: func TestSessionTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n468: \tif k8sClient == nil {\n469: \t\tt.Skip(\"Kubernetes client not available\")\n470: \t}\n471: \n472: \tmessage := map[string]string{\n473: \t\t\"message\": \"Short TTL test\",\n474: \t}\n475: \tbody, _ := json.Marshal(message)\n476: \n477: \treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/echo-agent-short-ttl\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n478: \tif err != nil {\n479: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create request: %v\", err)\n480: \t}\n481: \n482: \treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n483: \tif apiToken != \"\" {\n484: \t\treq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n485: \t}\n486: \n487: \tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n488: \tif err != nil {\n489: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Request failed: %v\", err)\n490: \t}\n491: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n492: \n493: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n494: \t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n495: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Short TTL test returned status: %d, body: %s\", resp.StatusCode, string(body))\n496: \t}\n497: \n498: \tt.Log(\"Short TTL agent invoked successfully, waiting for expiration...\")\n499: \n500: \ttime.Sleep(35 * time.Second)\n501: \n502: \tctx := context.Background()\n503: \tpods, err := k8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{\n504: \t\tLabelSelector: \"app=echo-agent-short-ttl\",\n505: \t})\n506: \tif err != nil {\n507: \t\tt.Logf(\"Failed to list pods after TTL: %v\", err)\n508: \t\treturn\n509: \t}\n510: \n511: \tt.Logf(\"Found %d pods after TTL expiration\", len(pods.Items))\n512: }\n513: \n514: func TestWarmPoolCodeInterpreter(t *testing.T) {\n515: \tcode := map[string]string{\n516: \t\t\"code\": \"import time; start = time.time(); print(f'Warm start: {time.time() - start:.3f}s')\",\n517: \t}\n518: \tbody, _ := json.Marshal(code)\n519: \n520: \treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/e2e-code-interpreter-warmpool\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n521: \tif err != nil {\n522: \t\tt.Skipf(\"Warm pool interpreter not available: %v\", err)\n523: \t}\n524: \n525: \treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n526: \tif apiToken != \"\" {\n527: \t\treq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+apiToken)\n528: \t}\n529: \n530: \tstartTime := time.Now()\n531: \tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n532: \telapsed := time.Since(startTime)\n533: \n534: \tif err != nil {\n535: \t\tt.Skipf(\"Warm pool request failed: %v\", err)\n536: \t}\n537: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n538: \n539: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n540: \t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n541: \t\tt.Logf(\"Warm pool returned status: %d, body: %s\", resp.StatusCode, string(body))\n542: \t\tt.Skip(\"Warm pool interpreter not configured\")\n543: \t}\n544: \n545: \tvar result map[string]interface{}\n546: \tif err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n547: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to decode response: %v\", err)\n548: \t}\n549: \n550: \tt.Logf(\"Warm pool response: %+v (latency: %v)\", result, elapsed)\n551: \n552: \tif elapsed > 5*time.Second {\n553: \t\tt.Logf(\"Warning: Warm pool latency (%v) higher than expected\", elapsed)\n554: \t}\n555: }\n556: \n557: func TestNamespaceIsolation(t *testing.T) {\n558: \tif k8sClient == nil {\n559: \t\tt.Skip(\"Kubernetes client not available\")\n560: \t}\n561: \n562: \tctx := context.Background()\n563: \n564: \tnsList, err := k8sClient.CoreV1().Namespaces().List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n565: \tif err != nil {\n566: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to list namespaces: %v\", err)\n567: \t}\n568: \n569: \tfoundAgentCube := false\n570: \tfor _, ns := range nsList.Items {\n571: \t\tif ns.Name == namespace {\n572: \t\t\tfoundAgentCube = true\n573: \t\t\tt.Logf(\"Found AgentCube namespace: %s\", ns.Name)\n574: \t\t\tbreak\n575: \t\t}\n576: \t}\n577: \n578: \tif !foundAgentCube {\n579: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"AgentCube namespace %s not found\", namespace)\n580: \t}\n581: }\n582: \n583: func TestResourceQuotas(t *testing.T) {\n584: \tif k8sClient == nil {\n585: \t\tt.Skip(\"Kubernetes client not available\")\n586: \t}\n587: \n588: \tctx := context.Background()\n589: \n590: \tresourceQuotas, err := k8sClient.CoreV1().ResourceQuotas(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n591: \tif err != nil {\n592: \t\tt.Logf(\"Failed to list resource quotas (may not be configured): %v\", err)\n593: \t\tt.Skip(\"Resource quotas not configured\")\n594: \t}\n595: \n596: \tif len(resourceQuotas.Items) > 0 {\n597: \t\tfor _, rq := range resourceQuotas.Items {\n598: \t\t\tt.Logf(\"Found resource quota: %s\", rq.Name)\n599: \t\t}\n600: \t} else {\n601: \t\tt.Skip(\"No resource quotas configured\")\n602: \t}\n603: }\n604: \n605: func TestConfigMapExists(t *testing.T) {\n606: \tif k8sClient == nil {\n607: \t\tt.Skip(\"Kubernetes client not available\")\n608: \t}\n609: \n610: \tctx := context.Background()\n611: \n612: \tconfigMaps, err := k8sClient.CoreV1().ConfigMaps(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{\n613: \t\tLabelSelector: \"app.kubernetes.io/name=agentcube\",\n614: \t})\n615: \tif err != nil {\n616: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to list ConfigMaps: %v\", err)\n617: \t}\n618: \n619: \tif len(configMaps.Items) == 0 {\n620: \t\tt.Skip(\"No AgentCube ConfigMaps found\")\n621: \t}\n622: \n623: \tfor _, cm := range configMaps.Items {\n624: \t\tt.Logf(\"Found ConfigMap: %s\", cm.Name)\n625: \t}\n626: }\n627: \n628: func TestServiceAccounts(t *testing.T) {\n629: \tif k8sClient == nil {\n630: \t\tt.Skip(\"Kubernetes client not available\")\n631: \t}\n632: \n633: \tctx := context.Background()\n634: \n635: \tsas, err := k8sClient.CoreV1().ServiceAccounts(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n636: \tif err != nil {\n637: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to list ServiceAccounts: %v\", err)\n638: \t}\n639: \n640: \tfoundWorkloadManager := false\n641: \tfoundRouter := false\n642: \n643: \tfor _, sa := range sas.Items {\n644: \t\tt.Logf(\"Found ServiceAccount: %s\", sa.Name)\n645: \t\tif sa.Name == \"workloadmanager\" || sa.Name == \"agentcube-workloadmanager\" {\n646: \t\t\tfoundWorkloadManager = true\n647: \t\t}\n648: \t\tif sa.Name == \"agentcube-router\" {\n649: \t\t\tfoundRouter = true\n650: \t\t}\n651: \t}\n652: \n653: \tif !foundWorkloadManager {\n654: \t\tt.Log(\"WorkloadManager ServiceAccount not found (may use default)\")\n655: \t}\n656: \tif !foundRouter {\n657: \t\tt.Log(\"Router ServiceAccount not found (may use default)\")\n658: \t}\n659: }\n\n(End of file - total 659 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// Copyright 2026 AgentCube Authors\n// E2E tests for AgentCube\n\npackage e2e\n\nimport (\n\t\"bytes\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"io\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/e2e_test.go","time":{"start":1775892237576,"end":1775892237602}}}}
